The paper discusses a technique for unsupervised learning using a multi-layer perceptron, which is a common approach in machine learning and artificial intelligence (cs.LG, cs.AI). The focus of the paper is on imputing missing values in datasets, which is a common problem in data mining and data analysis (cs.DM). The technique is evaluated with 24 datasets and 9 supervised learning algorithms, which suggests a focus on neural networks and other machine learning techniques (cs.NE). Finally, the paper discusses collaborative filtering and imputation techniques, which are commonly used in recommender systems and information retrieval (cs.SI).
